Business Brief -- American Stores Co.:
   Albertson's Inc. to Purchase
   74 Food and Drug Outlets
J.L. Scott, American Stores president and chief executive,
said a lack of adequate distribution facilities serving the
stores and a desire to concentrate on more profitable markets
contributed to the decision to sell the stores in Texas,
Oklahoma, Arkansas and Florida, along with a warehouse in
Ponca City, Okla. The deal is subject to final agreement and
certain legal requirements.
   Albertson's is a grocery chain headquartered in Boise,
Idaho.